Package: castSDM
Type: Package
Title: Causal-Aware Species Distribution Modeling
Version: 0.3.0
Author: Liqiang Q [aut, cre, cph] (ORCID: <https://orcid.org/0009-0002-6966-4633>)
Maintainer: Liqiang Q <2759831686@qq.com>
Authors@R: c(
    person(
            "Liqiang", "Q",
      email = "2759831686@qq.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
      comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0002-6966-4633")
    )
  )
Description: Integrates causal-aware invariant variable screening with
    species distribution modeling. Uses response-focused structural
    constraints, spatial-block effect invariance, bootstrap stability, and
    correlation-cluster redundancy control to select ecologically relevant
    predictors for transferable SDM. Legacy DAG and Markov Blanket screening
    remain available for audit and comparison. Fits an ensemble of standard
    SDM algorithms (Random Forest, BRT, MaxEnt, GAM) with performance-weighted
    ensemble prediction. Supports future climate projection via CMIP6 data
    and spatial cross-validation.
